content: Had a setback with our Rust code. A bug in the memory management slowed everything down. Back to the drawing board, but I'm learning so much about Rust's nuances.
Met with some traders today to pitch the mentorship idea. They're on board, but we need a solid structure. Xander's helping me design the curriculum.
Xander and I did a deep dive into cultural insights from my travels. We're mapping these onto market behaviors. It's like painting with data, and the patterns are fascinating.
Just got a call from a mentor. He's impressed with our progress and wants to join the mentorship program as an advisor. This is getting real.
Had a breakthrough with Xander's Rust code. Fixed the memory issue and now our trading sim is faster than ever. Gonna celebrate this win with some late-night coding.
Just wrapped up a multi-day session with Xander. We've got a working model that integrates behavioral econ into our trading strategies. Next up, real-world testing.
